{"data":{"talks":{"title":"Docker-Composing Your Way to a Better Development Environment","description_html":"<p>Development environments can become cumbersome over time, with setup occasionally filling multiple pages of documentation and making onboarding new team members a difficult task. Whether you deploy your Python application using containers or not, Docker Compose is a great tool for defining development environments that closely mirror production and can be spun up with a single command.</p>","abstract_html":"<p>By the end of this talk, audience members will understand the following concepts:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Running application services/dependencies inside containers and its advantages and disadvantages. </li>\n<li>Defining application environment and services via Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml configuration files.</li>\n<li>Managing the environment using the <code>docker-compose</code> CLI.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To illustrate these concepts, a Django application will be configured to use a database, a cache, a queue and task worker.</p>","feedback_url":"https://pyohio.typeform.com/to/JyfC8z","kind":"30-minute Talk","schedule":{"room":"Cartoon 2","start":"2019-07-27T15:00:00"},"speakers":[{"name":"Ricardo Solano","speaker_id":257,"photo":{"local":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":250,"height":250,"src":"/2019/static/7a81a000d97524dbfadcf219e1f642aa/d092e/257.png","srcSet":"/2019/static/7a81a000d97524dbfadcf219e1f642aa/d092e/257.png 1x"}}}}}],"youtube_url":"http://youtu.be/p1CQa0kvAq8"},"tutorials":null},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"5df8e4b9-8b70-5a47-a7f1-bb9268cac7f9"}}